recursividad.","author_name":"Chiste informático","tweet_button":"","tweet_button_label":"Tuitear","content_gap":{"unit":"px","size":10,"sizes":[]},"button_size":{"unit":"px","size":0.5,"sizes":[]},"quote_gap":{"unit":"px","size":0,"sizes":[]},"_background_background":"classic","__globals__":{"_background_color":"globals/colors?id=2c1b11c"}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"blockquote"},{"id":"9d9896d","elType":"widget","settings":{"title":"Los números de Fibonacci","size":"large","__globals__":{"typography_typography":"globals/typography?id=secondary"},"_padding":{"unit":"%","top":"3","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"_padding_tablet":{"unit":"%","top":"","right":"","bottom":"","left":"","isLinked":true},"_padding_mobile":{"unit":"%","top":"","right":"","bottom":"","left":"","isLinked":true},"header_size":"h3"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"heading"},{"id":"f75311f","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">Los primeros números de Fibonacci se definen de la siguiente forma:</span><br></p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>&nbsp;<span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size );">fibonacci(n)</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">&nbsp;=&nbsp;</span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size );">fibonacci(n-1) +&nbsp;</span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size );">fibonacci(n-2)</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">El i-ésimo número de fibonacci es igual a la suma de los dos anteriores.&nbsp;</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">Los números de Fibonacci tienen una gran cantidad de propiedades. Existe incluso, una revista, The Fibonacci Quarterly, con el objetivo de publicar teoremas que impliquen a los números de Fibonacci.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>Puesto que los números de Fibonacci se definen recursivamente, parece natural crear un método recursivo que lo resuelva. Este método, que se puede ver más abajo, y funciona sin ningún problema de forma teórica, sin embargo, pero tiene un gran problema.&nbsp;</p>
<p>En una ordenador rápido se tarda muchísimo tiempo en calcular Fibonacci de 50. Esto se traduce en una cantidad sin sentido de tiempo, ya que realmente se deben hacer solamente 49 sumas. El problema es que este método recursivo realiza muchos cálculos repetidos. Para calcular fibonacci(n) , calculamos recursivamente&nbsp;<span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px;">fibonacci</span>(n-l) . Cuando la llamada recursiva termina, calculamos&nbsp;<span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px;">fibonacci</span>(n-2) usando otra llamada recursiva. Pero en realidad ya se había calculado&nbsp;<span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );">fibonacci</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">(n -2) cuando hemos calculado&nbsp;</span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );">fibonacci</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">(n -1) , luego la llamada a&nbsp;</span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );">fibonacci</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">(n-2) de nuevo está repetida, y por ello, de nuevo se traduce en un calculo innecesario.&nbsp;</span></p>","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":20,"sizes":[]},"typography_font_weight":"400","typography_line_height":{"unit":"em","size":2,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"},{"id":"85ddc12","elType":"widget","settings":{"language":"java","code":"   //obtener el número de fibonacci de n
 static int fibonacci(int n) {     
  if(n <= 1) return n;                          //caso base
  else return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2);  //caso general   
 } ","theme":"okaidia"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"code-highlight"},{"id":"9d66382","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Normalmente, hacer dos llamadas a un método en lugar de una, suele duplicar el tiempo de ejecución de un programa, pero en este caso la situación es mucho peor, la llamada a fibonacci(n -1) como las llamadas a <span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px;">fibonacci</span>(n -2) hacen a su vez llamadas a <span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px;">fibonacci</span>(n-3), 10 que significa que hay en realidad tres llamadas a <span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );">fibonacci</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">(n -3 ) . A partir de ahí, la situación se vuelve todavía peor: las llamadas a </span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px;">fibonacci</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">(n-2) y a </span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px;">fibonacci</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">(n-3) producen llamadas a </span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px;">fibonacci</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">(n-4) , cinco en total. Obtenemos por tanto un efecto que se acumula de forma brutal: cada llamada recursiva produce más y más trabajo redundante. </span></p><p><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">En consecuencia, el número de llamadas recursivas es incluso mayor que el número de Fibonacci que queremos calcular. Por ejemplo, para N = 40, el resultado es 102.334.155, mientras que el número total de llamadas recursivas es mayor que 300 millones. No nos debemos sorprender si al calcular </span><span style="letter-spacing: 0.1px; color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight );">fibonacci(50)</span><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );"> el ordenador no es capaz de terminar, ya que un procesador actual podría tardar 10000 años en obtenerlo y necesitar más de 1x103 hexabytes de memoria RAM para poder almacenar semejante pila de llamadas. </span></p><p><span style="color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-size ); font-weight: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-weight ); letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-text-letter-spacing );">A continuación se puede observar el crecimiento del número de llamadas recursivas.</span></p>","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":20,"sizes":[]},"typography_font_weight":"400","typography_line_height":{"unit":"em","size":2,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"},{"id":"ee702d9","elType":"widget","settings":{"image":{"url":"https://aulaenlanube.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/traza-recursiva-fibonacci.webp","id":14240,"alt":"","source":"library"},"_padding":{"unit":"%","top":"2","right":"2","bottom":"2","left":"2","isLinked":true},"_padding_tablet":{"unit":"%","top":"","right":"","bottom":"","left":"","isLinked":true},"_padding_mobile":{"unit":"%","top":"","right":"","bottom":"","left":"","isLinked":true},"width":{"unit":"%","size":60,"sizes":[]},"image_size":"medium_large","align":"center","caption_source":"custom","caption":"Traza recursiva de los números de Fibonacci.","__globals__":{"caption_typography_typography":"globals/typography?id=4498f76"}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"image"},{"id":"05a55bc","elType":"widget","settings":{"html":"<script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
